WEBVTT

00:04.656 --> 00:06.356
Yeah, I just had lunch
with my husband

00:06.358 --> 00:07.824
and I'm on my way home.

00:07.826 --> 00:10.293
I have a lot to do
before the meeting tonight.

00:10.295 --> 00:13.363
Of course I'll be there, but I hope
there's more on the agenda

00:13.365 --> 00:14.797
than the charity ball.

00:14.799 --> 00:18.067
I don't want to debate
which caterer to use for an hour.

00:18.069 --> 00:20.336
I'd gladly
vote for corn dogs

00:20.338 --> 00:21.938
if it ends the meeting sooner.

00:21.940 --> 00:24.140
See you tonight.

00:25.176 --> 00:28.011
And that was the last known
sighting of Sophie Troy,

00:28.013 --> 00:30.213
at 2:37 p.m.
on a surveillance video.

00:30.215 --> 00:32.649
She was coming from having
lunch with her husband,

00:32.651 --> 00:36.085
and she was going home using
the congressional underground tunnels.

00:36.087 --> 00:37.520
Ok, so it's 3 a.m. now.

00:37.522 --> 00:39.322
She's been gone
a little over 12 hours.

00:39.324 --> 00:41.157
That doesn't qualify
as a missing person yet.

00:41.159 --> 00:43.860
The director's personally
asked us to handle the case.

00:43.862 --> 00:45.862
Her husband is Congressman
Benjamin Troy,

00:45.864 --> 00:47.830
which makes her a VIP.

00:47.832 --> 00:49.566
Well, the question is,
who's the real target,

00:49.568 --> 00:50.934
Sophie or her husband?

00:50.936 --> 00:52.902
I mean, is this an attempt
to influence him?

00:52.904 --> 00:54.837
Well, the Congressman
isn't very high profile.

00:54.839 --> 00:57.373
It's his first term, and he has views
which have made him

00:57.375 --> 00:59.542
unpopular on both sides
of the aisle.

00:59.544 --> 01:01.811
Sophie's a healthcare
lawyer on the D.C. museum board.

01:01.813 --> 01:03.880
What was her schedule
after lunch? Do you know?

01:03.882 --> 01:05.447
Yeah. She was gonna
go home,

01:05.450 --> 01:07.517
and then she had
a foundation meeting at 7:00.

01:07.519 --> 01:08.651
She didn't make either.

01:08.653 --> 01:10.153
Then when she wasn't home
by 12:30,

01:10.155 --> 01:11.654
the Congressman called
family and friends

01:11.656 --> 01:13.489
before contacting
Capitol police at 1:45.

01:13.491 --> 01:15.391
We were notified
a half an hour later.

01:15.393 --> 01:17.126
Let's go back
to her last sighting.

01:17.128 --> 01:19.762
Do we have the surveillance footage
from the other side of the stairwell?

01:19.764 --> 01:21.864
Yeah. That would be
the Library of Congress lobby

01:21.866 --> 01:23.066
and there's no sign of her.

01:23.068 --> 01:24.968
It's like she vanished
into thin air.

01:24.970 --> 01:28.071
Guys, it is possible
she just left of her own accord.

01:28.073 --> 01:30.039
But we have to assume
it's a kidnapping

01:30.041 --> 01:31.608
unless proven otherwise.

01:31.610 --> 01:34.711
Well, we know she was
on the phone before she disappeared.

01:34.713 --> 01:37.313
We need to pull all her email
and cell phone records.

01:37.315 --> 01:40.249
The Congressman's here.

01:40.251 --> 01:42.018
Have a seat,
Congressman.

01:42.020 --> 01:44.020
I've heard the statistics.
What do we have,

01:44.022 --> 01:45.521
36 hours or something
to save her?

01:45.523 --> 01:47.390
In a homicide, the first 48 hours
are the most critical,

01:47.392 --> 01:49.626
but in an abduction,
every minute counts.

01:49.628 --> 01:51.194
Oh, God.

01:51.196 --> 01:54.197
We don't know for sure
that there's been foul play.

01:54.199 --> 01:56.165
No. No, no.
I know my wife.

01:56.167 --> 01:58.735
We just had our
first anniversary a week ago.

01:58.737 --> 02:00.036
She wouldn't just leave me,

02:00.038 --> 02:02.605
certainly not without
getting the last word in.

02:02.607 --> 02:05.041
Is there anyone
who would want to hurt her?

02:05.043 --> 02:06.709
No. No, no.

02:06.711 --> 02:10.013
Sophie's a wonderful,
sweet woman.

02:10.014 --> 02:11.881
I, on the other hand,

02:11.883 --> 02:14.183
I'm not very well-liked
in this town.

02:14.185 --> 02:16.552
And who are your enemies?

02:16.554 --> 02:18.254
Well, where do we begin?

02:18.256 --> 02:20.490
We have the oil lobbies.

02:20.492 --> 02:23.459
Uh, we have the NRA
and PETA.

02:23.461 --> 02:26.162
You have an equal
opportunity offender.

02:26.164 --> 02:27.830
Plus, then there's
all the other oddballs

02:27.832 --> 02:29.332
who call, write letters,
send emails.

02:29.334 --> 02:31.501
My aides don't usually
show them to me, though.

02:31.503 --> 02:33.336
We'll need to see those.

02:33.338 --> 02:34.804
Yeah, I'll have my office
send them over.

02:34.806 --> 02:37.306
And also let them know
that we're on an information lockdown.

02:37.308 --> 02:41.678
Our chances of solving this are better
if the media doesn't get wind of it.

02:41.680 --> 02:43.946
You know, I understand
people being angry with me,

02:43.948 --> 02:45.715
but to take it out
on my family,

02:45.717 --> 02:47.016
on Sophie...

02:47.018 --> 02:50.053
Rest assured,
you're our priority.

02:53.458 --> 02:54.624
Excuse me.

02:55.894 --> 02:58.861
The tech analysis from the video
surveillance came back.

02:58.863 --> 03:00.463
The footage from
the Library of Congress

03:00.465 --> 03:01.964
where there's no sign
of Sophie

03:01.966 --> 03:03.466
is an old video
on a continuous loop.

03:03.468 --> 03:04.801
Someone hacked the system?

03:04.803 --> 03:06.736
It's run by the Metro P.D.
it's outdated.

03:06.738 --> 03:08.671
It wouldn't take
a lot of brainpower to get in.

03:08.673 --> 03:10.339
I have just received
confirmation

03:10.341 --> 03:11.641
authorities have been alerted

03:11.643 --> 03:14.210
and are treating this
as a probable abduction.

03:14.212 --> 03:16.412
Just to recap, Sophie Troy,

03:16.414 --> 03:18.247
wife of Congressman
Benjamin Troy,

03:18.249 --> 03:21.150
has been missing since
mid-afternoon yesterday.

03:21.152 --> 03:22.919
At this time, authorities
have not said when...

03:22.921 --> 03:24.253
What's going on?
Who leaked this?

03:24.255 --> 03:25.621
I don't know.

03:25.623 --> 03:26.956
Hotch.

03:26.958 --> 03:30.126
The last call Sophie made
was to a lawyer on vacation.

03:30.128 --> 03:32.328
This is her voicemail.

03:33.498 --> 03:36.132
Hi, Tania, it's Sophie,
and I'm still out of town--

03:36.134 --> 03:37.100
oops--sorry.

03:37.102 --> 03:38.701
What are you doing?

03:38.703 --> 03:39.902
Stop, let go of me!

03:39.904 --> 03:42.098
No--aah!

